Filling the null values with column mode¶

In [15]:
def fill_na_mode(df):
    for column in df.columns:
        cmode = df[column].mode()[0]
        df[column].fillna(cmode,inplace=True)
    return df
new_df = fill_na_mode(data_df)

Trimming Outliers¶

In [25]:
def iqr_trim(df):
    for column in ["age_of_car","age_of_policyholder","population_density"]:
        Q1 = df[column].quantile(0.25)
        Q3 = df[column].quantile(0.75)
        IQR = Q3-Q1
        LB = Q1 - 1.5*IQR
        UB = Q3 + 1.5*IQR
        df = df[(df[column]>=LB) & (df[column]<=UB)]
    return df
trim_df = iqr_trim(new_df)

In [29]:






def hist_pltr(cdf,column):
    claim_df=cdf[cdf['is_claim']==1]
    no_claim_df=cdf[cdf['is_claim']==0]

    fig ,axes = plt.subplots(1,3,figsize=(12,3))

    #All data
    axes[0].hist(cdf[column],bins=20,edgecolor='black')
    axes[0].set_title(f'{column}-All_data')
    axes[0].set_xlabel(column)
    axes[0].set_ylabel('Frequrncy')

    #Data without claim
    axes[1].hist(no_claim_df[column],bins=20,edgecolor='black')
    axes[1].set_title(f'{column}-Without_claim')
    axes[1].set_xlabel(column)
    axes[1].set_ylabel('Frequrncy')
    
    #Data with claim
    axes[2].hist(claim_df[column],bins=20,edgecolor='black')
    axes[2].set_title(f'{column}-With_claim')
    axes[2].set_xlabel(column)
    axes[2].set_ylabel('Frequrncy')

In [31]:






def hist_pt(cdf,column):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))

    sns.histplot(data=cdf,x=column,hue="is_claim",multiple="stack",bins=20,edgecolor="black")
    plt.title(f'{column} - Classification on is_claim')
    plt.xlabel(column)
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
